---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "Age Calculator - Exact Age in Years, Months & Days",
  description: "Calculate your exact age down to the day. Find out how many days you've been alive, your half-birthday, and the precise time between any two dates with this free tool.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Age Calculator - Exact Age in Years, Months & Days",
    "description": "Calculate exact age and duration between dates in years, months, and days with this free interactive tool.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "SiliconBased"
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-03-15"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does this age calculator handle leap years?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Our calculator uses standard calendar math, which automatically accounts for leap years. It checks if February has 28 or 29 days in the specific years being calculated, ensuring your total day count is exactly right."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use this to find the time between any two dates?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes! While it's designed to calculate your age by comparing your birth date to today, you can change the 'Calculate age at this date' field to any past or future date to find the exact duration between two points in time."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why do some months have 30 days and others 31?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Gregorian calendar, which is the international standard, has months of varying lengths for historical reasons dating back to Roman times. This irregular structure is why calculating exact age requires more complex math than simple division."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is chronological age vs biological age?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Chronological age is the exact amount of time you have been alive since birth, which this tool calculates. Biological age refers to how old your cells and tissues appear based on physiology, which can be affected by lifestyle, diet, and genetics."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many days are in a year?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A standard calendar year has 365 days. However, a leap year, which occurs almost every four years, has 366 days. In astronomy, a solar year (the time it takes Earth to orbit the sun) is approximately 365.2422 days."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout
  site="siliconbased"
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/age-calculator"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Age Calculator</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Calculate your exact age in years, months, and days, or find the duration between any two dates.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <div class="input-section">
          <div class="input-group">
            <label for="birthDate">Date of Birth</label>
            <input type="date" id="birthDate">
            <div id="dateError" class="error-msg">Please enter a valid birth date. Target date must be after birth date.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="input-group">
            <label for="targetDate">Calculate age at this date</label>
            <input type="date" id="targetDate">
            <div class="helper-text">Defaults to today's date</div>
          </div>

          <button id="todayBtn" class="secondary-btn">Set to Today</button>
        </div>

        <div class="output-section">
          <div class="result-card highlight">
            <div class="result-label">Age</div>
            <div class="result-value" id="mainAgeResult">--</div>
            <div class="result-sub" id="ymdResult">Enter your birth date to calculate.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="stats-grid hidden" id="extraStats">
            <div class="stat-box">
              <div class="stat-label">Total Months</div>
              <div class="stat-value" id="totalMonths">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-box">
              <div class="stat-label">Total Weeks</div>
              <div class="stat-value" id="totalWeeks">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-box">
              <div class="stat-label">Total Days</div>
              <div class="stat-value" id="totalDays">--</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-box">
              <div class="stat-label">Next Birthday</div>
              <div class="stat-value" id="nextBirthday">--</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>The Complexities of Calculating Age</h2>

      <p>Calculating someone's age seems like it should be one of the simplest math problems in the world. However, if you've ever tried to calculate exactly how many months and days old you are, you quickly realize that the human calendar is a messy, irregular system. Our age calculator does the heavy lifting to provide your precise chronological age, down to the exact day.</p>

      <h3>Why Calendar Math is Hard</h3>
      <p>If we lived in a simulation where every month had 30 days and every year had 360 days, finding the duration between two dates would be simple arithmetic. But the Gregorian calendar—the standard calendar used across most of the globe—is notoriously irregular.</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Months vary in length, containing 28, 29, 30, or 31 days.</li>
        <li>A standard year is 365 days long.</li>
        <li>A leap year occurs almost every four years and is 366 days long.</li>
        <li>Leap year rules have exceptions: century years (like 1900) are not leap years unless they are divisible by 400 (like 2000).</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Because of these irregularities, "one month ago" means something different depending on the date. One month before March 15th is February 15th (an exact 28 or 29-day difference). But one month before May 31st? April only has 30 days, so does "one month ago" mean April 30th? Calendar math requires specific rules to handle these edge cases, which is why manual calculations are prone to error.</p>

      <h3>How We Calculate Exact Age</h3>
      <p>To calculate age accurately in Years, Months, and Days, algorithms don't just count the total number of days and divide by 365. That would ignore the nuance of specific months.</p>

      <p>Instead, the calculation works backwards from the target date to the start date:</p>

      <div class="formula-box">
        1. <strong>Days:</strong> Subtract the birth day from the target day. If the result is negative, borrow a month from the target month, and add the number of days in the previous month to the days tally.<br><br>
        2. <strong>Months:</strong> Subtract the birth month from the target month. If negative, borrow a year, and add 12 to the months tally.<br><br>
        3. <strong>Years:</strong> Subtract the birth year from the target year.
      </div>

      <p>This method ensures that if you were born on January 15th, and today is March 14th, you are 2 months minus 1 day old, exactly calculated based on whether it was a leap year or not.</p>

      <h3>Chronological vs. Biological Age</h3>
      <p>While this tool calculates your <strong>chronological age</strong> (the exact amount of time that has passed since you were born), the scientific community is increasingly interested in <strong>biological age</strong>.</p>

      <p>Chronological age moves at exactly the same speed for everyone. Biological age, however, measures how quickly your body is aging at a cellular level. It is influenced by genetics, diet, stress, sleep, exercise, and environment. Two people might both have a chronological age of exactly 45 years, 3 months, and 12 days, but one might have the biological markers of a 35-year-old, while the other has the physiology of a 55-year-old.</p>

      <h3>Programming Date Calculations</h3>
      <p>For developers, handling dates is an infamous pain point. In JavaScript, for example, the native <code>Date</code> object uses a zero-indexed month system (January is 0, December is 11), but one-indexed days. Timestamps are calculated in milliseconds since the Unix Epoch (January 1, 1970). Because building custom date logic is so fraught with edge-case bugs related to timezones and leap years, developers almost always rely on specialized libraries like Date-fns, Moment.js, or the modern Intl APIs to handle date parsing.</p>

      <p>Speaking of calculations that developers often need to build into their applications, if you are working on an e-commerce or restaurant platform, you might also need to calculate percentages. Check out our <a href="/tip-calculator">Tip Calculator</a> to see how we handle real-time percentage and bill-splitting math.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>How does this age calculator handle leap years?</summary>
        <p>Our calculator uses native browser date mathematics, which automatically account for leap years. It knows exactly which years are leap years (including the century rules) and whether February had 28 or 29 days in the specific years between your birth date and the target date.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I use this to find the time between any two dates?</summary>
        <p>Yes! While it's designed to calculate your age by comparing your birth date to today, you can change the "Calculate age at this date" field to any past or future date. This makes it perfect for finding the exact duration of a project, relationship, or historical era.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Why do some months have 30 days and others 31?</summary>
        <p>The Gregorian calendar has months of varying lengths for historical and political reasons dating back to the Roman Empire. The original Roman calendar was 10 months long. Later emperors, including Julius Caesar and Augustus, reformed the calendar, leading to the irregular 28/30/31 day structure we use today to keep the calendar roughly aligned with the solar year.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is chronological age vs biological age?</summary>
        <p>Chronological age is the exact, unchangeable amount of time you have been alive since birth, which this tool calculates. Biological age refers to how old your cells and tissues appear based on physiology, which can be positively or negatively affected by your lifestyle, diet, genetics, and environment.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How many days are in a year?</summary>
        <p>A standard calendar year has 365 days. However, a leap year, which occurs almost every four years, has 366 days. In astronomy, a solar year (the exact time it takes the Earth to complete one full orbit around the sun) is approximately 365.24219 days.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const birthDateInput = document.getElementById('birthDate');
    const targetDateInput = document.getElementById('targetDate');
    const todayBtn = document.getElementById('todayBtn');

    const mainAgeResult = document.getElementById('mainAgeResult');
    const ymdResult = document.getElementById('ymdResult');
    const dateError = document.getElementById('dateError');
    const extraStats = document.getElementById('extraStats');

    const totalMonthsEl = document.getElementById('totalMonths');
    const totalWeeksEl = document.getElementById('totalWeeks');
    const totalDaysEl = document.getElementById('totalDays');
    const nextBirthdayEl = document.getElementById('nextBirthday');

    // Initialize target date to today
    const setToday = () => {
      const today = new Date();
      // Format YYYY-MM-DD local time
      const yyyy = today.getFullYear();
      const mm = String(today.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');
      const dd = String(today.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
      targetDateInput.value = `${yyyy}-${mm}-${dd}`;
    };

    setToday();

    const calculateAge = () => {
      if (!birthDateInput.value || !targetDateInput.value) return;

      const birthDate = new Date(birthDateInput.value + 'T00:00:00');
      const targetDate = new Date(targetDateInput.value + 'T00:00:00');

      if (isNaN(birthDate.getTime()) || isNaN(targetDate.getTime())) return;

      if (birthDate > targetDate) {
        dateError.style.display = 'block';
        extraStats.classList.add('hidden');
        mainAgeResult.textContent = '--';
        ymdResult.textContent = 'Invalid date range.';
        return;
      } else {
        dateError.style.display = 'none';
      }

      // Calculate exact Y, M, D
      let years = targetDate.getFullYear() - birthDate.getFullYear();
      let months = targetDate.getMonth() - birthDate.getMonth();
      let days = targetDate.getDate() - birthDate.getDate();

      if (days < 0) {
        months--;
        // Get days in the previous month of target year
        const prevMonth = new Date(targetDate.getFullYear(), targetDate.getMonth(), 0);
        days += prevMonth.getDate();
      }

      if (months < 0) {
        years--;
        months += 12;
      }

      // Render Main Result
      mainAgeResult.textContent = years.toString();

      let ymdString = [];
      if (years > 0) ymdString.push(`${years} ${years === 1 ? 'year' : 'years'}`);
      if (months > 0) ymdString.push(`${months} ${months === 1 ? 'month' : 'months'}`);
      if (days > 0 || ymdString.length === 0) ymdString.push(`${days} ${days === 1 ? 'day' : 'days'}`);

      ymdResult.textContent = ymdString.join(', ');

      // Calculate Extras
      const timeDiff = targetDate.getTime() - birthDate.getTime();
      const dayDiff = Math.floor(timeDiff / (1000 * 3600 * 24));

      const totalMonthsCalc = (years * 12) + months;
      const totalWeeksCalc = Math.floor(dayDiff / 7);

      // Next birthday
      const currentYear = targetDate.getFullYear();
      let nextBday = new Date(currentYear, birthDate.getMonth(), birthDate.getDate());

      if (nextBday < targetDate) {
        nextBday.setFullYear(currentYear + 1);
      }

      const nextBdayDiff = Math.ceil((nextBday.getTime() - targetDate.getTime()) / (1000 * 3600 * 24));

      // Render Extras
      extraStats.classList.remove('hidden');

      totalMonthsEl.textContent = new Intl.NumberFormat().format(totalMonthsCalc);
      totalWeeksEl.textContent = new Intl.NumberFormat().format(totalWeeksCalc);
      totalDaysEl.textContent = new Intl.NumberFormat().format(dayDiff);

      if (nextBdayDiff === 0) {
        nextBirthdayEl.textContent = "Today! 🎉";
      } else {
        nextBirthdayEl.textContent = `in ${nextBdayDiff} ${nextBdayDiff === 1 ? 'day' : 'days'}`;
      }
    };

    // Event Listeners
    birthDateInput.addEventListener('input', calculateAge);
    targetDateInput.addEventListener('input', calculateAge);

    todayBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      setToday();
      calculateAge();
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }

    .calculator-container { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }

    .calc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .calc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
    }

    .input-section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .input-group label { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.95rem; }

    input[type="date"] { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.85rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; width: 100%; font-size: 1.1rem; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: inherit; }
    input[type="date"]:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }

    .helper-text { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .error-msg { color: #ef4444; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; display: none; }

    .secondary-btn { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: all 0.2s; align-self: flex-start; }
    .secondary-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent-color); color: var(--accent-color); }

    .output-section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: flex-start; }

    .result-card { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; text-align: center; }
    .result-card.highlight { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); }

    .result-label { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .result-value { font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .result-card.highlight .result-value { color: var(--accent-color); }
    .result-sub { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); font-weight: 500; }

    .stats-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
    .stats-grid.hidden { display: none; }

    .stat-box { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1rem; text-align: center; }
    .stat-label { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-weight: 600; }
    .stat-value { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); }

    .explainer { margin-top: 3rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .explainer h2, .explainer h3, .explainer h4 { color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .explainer h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; }
    .explainer h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; }
    .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .explainer a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    .explainer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .formula-box { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 5%, transparent); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color); padding: 1.25rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-family: monospace; font-size: 1.05rem; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; line-height: 1.5; }

    .faq-section { margin-top: 4rem; }
    .faq-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1.25rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
    .faq-section summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .faq-section summary::after { content: '+'; color: var(--accent-color); font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1; }
    .faq-section details[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
    .faq-section p { margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
